a\u00f1ol maya y La mano de Obreg\u00f3n\n| DirectedBy      = Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle \n| WrittenBy       = Fran Hevia & Mario Santiago Jim\u00e9nez \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|2|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 76181D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 19\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = El Tigre de Santa Julia, Papa Doc, Gardel\n| DirectedBy      = Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle, Leonardo Rodr\u00edguez & Marco Romano\n| WrittenBy       = Fran Hevia & Mario Santiago Jim\u00e9nez \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|9|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 76181D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 20\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = La historia del mole y Miss viuda negra\n| DirectedBy      = Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle \n| WrittenBy       = Fran Hevia & Mario Santiago Jim\u00e9nez \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|16|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 76181D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 21\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Zovek, Rey Lagarto y Lombardo\n| DirectedBy      = Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle, Leonardo Rodr\u00edguez & Marco Romano\n| WrittenBy       = Fran Hevia & Mario Santiago Jim\u00e9nez \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|30|df=yes}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 76181D\n}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|5472884}}\n\n[[Category:2016 Mexican television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Mexican television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Mexican television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Comedy Central original programming]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Mexican television series based on American television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American sketch comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Television series featuring reenactments]]\n[[Category:Fiction with unreliable narrators]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Mexican television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Drunk History\n| image                = Drunk History, el lado borroso de la historia.jpg\n| caption              = \n| show_name_2          = \n| genre                = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Educational television|Education]] \n* [[Television comedy|Comedy]]\n}}\n| creator              = \n| based_on             =  {{Based on|''[[Drunk History]]''}}\n| developer            = \n| writer               = {{Plainlist|\n* David Hern\u00e1ndez Miranda\n* Mario Santiago Jim\u00e9nez\n* Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle\n* Fran Hevia\n}}\n| screenplay           = \n| story                = \n| director             = {{Plainlist|\n* Leonardo Rodr\u00edguez\t\n* Jerry Rodr\u00edguez Burckle\n* Marco Romano\n}}\n| creative_director    = \n| presenter            = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Eugenio Derbez]]<ref name=\"cttrentals\" />\n}}\n| narrated             = \n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| endtheme             = \n| composer             = \n| country              = Mexico\n| language             = Spanish\n| num_seasons          = 3<!-- Or num_series. Increment when new seasons/series begin. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| num_episodes         = 21<!-- Value is incremented when new episodes air. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| list_episodes        = #Episodes\n| executive_producer   = Omar Rodr\u00edguez\n| producer             = \n| news_editor          = <!-- Content editor or editors of a current affairs/political show such as Newsnight. -->\n| location             = <!-- Nation the series was filmed in, if different from the nation of origin. -->\n| cinematography       = \n| animator             = \n| editor               = <!-- Film editors -->\n| camera               = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime              = <!-- Reliable source required -->\n| company              = [[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]]\n| distributor          = \n| budget               = \n| network              = [[Comedy Central (Latin American TV channel)|Comedy Central Latin America]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format         = [[Stereophonic sound]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2016|2|8|df=yes}}\n| last_aired           = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| related              = ''[[Drunk History (British TV series)|Drunk History]]'' (UK)\n| website              = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata; use |website_title= to change the display title. -->\n| production_website   = \n}}\n\n'''''Drunk History: El lado borroso de la historia''''', or simply '''''Drunk History''''', is a Mexican adaptation of the [[Drunk History|American television series of the same name]], which in turn is based on the web series ''[[Funny or Die]]''.<ref name=\"newslinereport\">{{cite web |title=Comedy Central estrena nueva temporada de 'Drunk history' |url=https://www.newslinereport.com/tv-paga/nota/comedy-central-estrena-nueva-temporada-de-drunk-history-2 |website=newslinereport.com |accessdate=28 September 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"cttrentals\">{{cite web |title=Drunk History 'El lado borroso de la historia' |url=http://www.cttrentals.com/mundo-ctt/2016/10/12/drunk-history-el-lado-borroso-de-la-historia/ |website=cttrentals.com |accessdate=28 September 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref> The series revolves around a narrator, who with his favorite alcoholic beverage, recounts a historical episode in front of the camera. Each story is interpreted by a group of actors that tries to represent the occurrences of the drunk.<ref name=\"newslinereport\" /> The series premiered on 8 February 2016 on [[Comedy Central (Latin American TV channel)|Comedy Central Latin America]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Woodside |first1=Maxine |title=\"Drunk History\" estrena este lunes por Comedy Central |url=https://www.radioformula.com.mx/entretenimiento/20160208/drunk-history-estrena-este-lunes-por-comedy-central-con-maxine-woodside/ |website=Radio F\u00f3rmula |publisher=Grupo F\u00f3rmula |accessdate=28 September 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n=== Regular cast ===\n* [[Eugenio Derbez]] as Himself<ref name=\"cttrentals\" />\n* [[Javier Noriega]] as Various roles\n\n=== Notable guest stars ===\n* [[Alfonso Herrera]] as [[Aquiles Serd\u00e1n]] / [[Ernesto \"Che\" Guevara]]\n* Marco Trevi\u00f1o as [[Porfirio D\u00edaz]] \n* [[Roberto Flores]] as [[Fidel Castro]]\n* [[Bruno Bichir]] as [[Crist\u00f3bal Col\u00f3n]]\n* [[Ana de la Reguera]] as Amada Diaz\n* [[Luis Gerardo M\u00e9ndez]] as [[Hern\u00e1n Cort\u00e9s]]\n* [[Ana Claudia Talanc\u00f3n]] as [[La G\u00fcera Rodr\u00edguez]]\n* [[Gerardo Taracena]] as [[Nezahualcoyotl (tlatoani)|Nezahualc\u00f3yotl]]\n* Roberto Sosa as [[Agust\u00edn Lara]]\n* [[Jes\u00fas Zavala]] as [[Joselito (singer)|Joselito]]\n* [[Liz Gallardo]] as [[Frida Kahlo]]\n* Miguel Rodarte as [[Antonio L\u00f3pez de Santa Anna]]\n* [[Christian Tappan]] as Flaco\n* [[Alejandro Calva]] as [[Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla|Miguel Hidalgo]]\n* Mar\u00eda del Carmen F\u00e9lix as [[Mar\u00eda F\u00e9lix]]\n* Ianis Guerrero as [[Emiliano Zapata|Zapata]]\n* [[Erick El\u00edas]] as [[Avila Camacho|\u00c1vila Camacho]]\n* [[Christian V\u00e1zquez]] as [[Emiliano Zapata]]\n* [[Sofia Ni\u00f1o de Rivera]] as Herself\n* [[Erik Hayser]] as [[Gonzalo Guerrero]]\n* [[Viviana Serna]] as [[Manuela S\u00e1enz]]\n* H\u00e9ctor Berzunza as [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar]]\n\n== Episodes ==\n=== Series overview ===\n{{Series overview\n| link1     = #Season 1 (2016)\n| color1    = #3D0102\n| episodes1 = 4\n| start1    = {{Start date|2016|2|8|df=yes}}\n| end1      = {{End date|2016|2|29|df=yes}}\n\n| link2     = #Season 2 (2016)\n| color2    = #A01920\n| episodes2 = 9\n| start2    = {{Start date|2016|9|5|df=yes}}\n| end2      = {{End date|2016|11|7|df=yes}}\n\n| link3     = #Season 3 (2017)\n| color3    = #76181D